			<title><![CDATA[October '13 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?75853-October-13-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 30 Sep 2013 05:20:46 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>This is it, the month with the most major new releases in the year. Please bear with me as I try to highlight, well, everything. :o 
 
The three biggest games this month are undoubtedly *Battlefield 4*, *Assassins Creed IV*, and *Batman: Arkham Origins*. All are known quantities, and everyone...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>This is it, the month with the most major new releases in the year. Please bear with me as I try to highlight, well, everything. :o<br />
<br />
The three biggest games this month are undoubtedly <b>Battlefield 4</b>, <b>Assassins Creed IV</b>, and <b>Batman: Arkham Origins</b>. All are known quantities, and everyone reading this likely already has an idea whether or not one of these is something they would be interested in. I am personally wary of franchise fatigue with the latter two. Batman is also getting sidescrolling beat-em up spinoffs on the Vita and 3DS. Rounding out the multiplatform games is a new <b>Lego</b> game (Marvel themed) and a new <b>Skylanders</b> game.<br />
<br />
The <b>PS3</b> continues it's end of generation domination a month before &quot;next&quot; next gen launches. <b>Beyond: Two Souls</b> is the big one, the next cinematic styled game from David Cage starring Ellen Page. This title has had several ups and downs ever since they announced it, cross your fingers if you are into this sort of thing. The platform is also getting a new budget adventure game in the style of Ico called <b>Rain</b>. You play as a boy (and possibly girl) spirit in a dreary world that is always raining. Objects, player characters, and enemies, can only be seen by the rain falling on where they are. Finally, a sequel to the original Disgaea is coming out, this time finally with a new HD art style. <b>Disgaea D2: A Brighter Darkness</b>.<br />
<br />
The <b>Wii U</b> has another decent month. The physical re-release of <b>The Legend of Zelda: The Wind Waker</b> comes out, if you didn't already download it last month, as well as a Sonic game with a fair amount of hype with a similar world platforming style as Mario Galaxy's. <b>Sonic: Lost World</b>, which is also getting a 3DS version.<br />
<br />
The <b>3DS</b> is getting an even bigger selection this month. <b>Pokemon X/Y</b> being the biggest, but it is also getting a new <b>Rune Factory</b>, a new <b>Etrian Odyssey</b>, and a new <b>Phoenix Wright</b> game.<br />
<br />
<br />
